<span id="freeTextContainer11568436248289851455">One of my favorite books. The anime is also really well done. A word of caution to the reader, however. You&apos;ll get more out of this book if you avoid trying to attribute social withdrawal, lolicon, etc. to some kind of Japanese pathology (because they&apos;re not). Instead, look at it as a frank and darkly comedic portrayal of the way people choose to cope with fear and feelings of inadequacy in modern times.</span>
